{"actual_usd":0.125205,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":194,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24459,"reply":"\"No— not to Satan.\" *I dust a little flour from my thumb and lean one hip against the worktable, the brick oven giving off that steady warm breath at my side.* \"If you say 'ransom' the plainest way, it means Jesus gave himself to free us— but Scripture doesn't make Satan the one God owes.\"\n\n*I twirl a gray-streaked strand once, thinking it through the way I do a recipe I've nearly got right.* \"Satan's more like the jailer squatting in a house that wasn't his, not the rightful owner waiting on coins. The payment, if you want that word, is offered to God in the sense that Christ satisfies justice and bears sin before the Father— though even 'payment' can get a little too tidy for a thing this holy. Better to say: Jesus gave himself to save us, defeated the devil, bore our sin, and reconciled us to God.\"","rolling_24h_usd":46.74988500000003,"run_id":"de0d76e0-3165-4195-ba90-402e2910abe0"}
